Makes the LLVM toolchain binaries (clang, lld, llvm-*) LOAD and run on
Windows XP/2000. lib/Support's Windows code statically imports six Vista+/
Win7+ functions (GetFinalPathNameByHandleW, SetFileInformationByHandle, and
the processor-group APIs GetLogicalProcessorInformationEx /
Get|Set ThreadGroupAffinity / GetProcessGroupAffinity); a static import of a
missing function makes the whole .exe fail to start on pre-Vista. Resolve
them dynamically via GetProcAddress (as LLVM already does for
PrefetchVirtualMemory) and fall back: realPathFromHandle fails soft, rename
uses MoveFileExW by path, and the processor-group code collapses to a single
GetSystemInfo group with no thread-group affinity.

